==English==

===Etymology===
Originally "to feel around", possibly metathesis of {{OE.}} ''[[græpsan]]'' "to touch, feel," from Proto-Germanic ''*graipison''.

===Verb===
'''to grasp''' ([[grasps]], [[grasped]], [[grasping]])

# To [[grip]]
# To [[understand]]

